24/06/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The cabinet approved a privatisation strategy Thursday (23 June) for the sale of Bulgarian defence sector plants but is leaving details of the process to the next administration. 
Parliamentary elections will be held Saturday. 
According to the privatisation strategy, holdings will be sold in a two-stage procedure. 
Most of the focus will be placed on price, though the stategy also calls for securing favourable investment arrangements and social benefits. 
(Sega - 24/06/05; Mediapool - 23/06/05)
